00:01:46.866 --> 00:01:47.916 A:middle
When you first open a

00:01:47.916 --> 00:01:49.616 A:middle
playground, Xcode shows you the

00:01:49.756 --> 00:01:50.516 A:middle
standard editor.

00:01:51.386 --> 00:01:52.736 A:middle
This is the basic editor mode

00:01:52.736 --> 00:01:54.646 A:middle
you use in Xcode with a couple

00:01:54.646 --> 00:01:55.286 A:middle
additions.

00:01:56.286 --> 00:01:57.726 A:middle
What is unique about this editor

00:01:57.916 --> 00:01:59.426 A:middle
when you're in a playground is

00:01:59.426 --> 00:02:00.866 A:middle
the result sidebar on the right

00:01:59.426 --> 00:02:00.866 A:middle
the result sidebar on the right

00:02:00.866 --> 00:02:02.736 A:middle
hands side displaying the result

00:02:02.736 --> 00:02:04.236 A:middle
of each expression in your code.

00:02:06.146 --> 00:02:07.836 A:middle
You also have the ability to add

00:02:07.836 --> 00:02:09.716 A:middle
these results as inline results.

00:02:10.916 --> 00:02:12.246 A:middle
This is done by selecting the

00:02:12.246 --> 00:02:14.256 A:middle
rectangular button beside your

00:02:14.256 --> 00:02:15.476 A:middle
result in the result sidebar.

00:02:16.916 --> 00:02:18.276 A:middle
This will then show your result

00:02:18.276 --> 00:02:22.916 A:middle
inline with your Swift Code.

00:02:22.916 --> 00:02:24.406 A:middle
In this example you can see this

00:02:24.406 --> 00:02:25.646 A:middle
demonstrated where "Hello,

00:02:25.746 --> 00:02:27.746 A:middle
playground" is added below our

00:02:27.746 --> 00:02:29.236 A:middle
string variable declaration.

00:02:31.606 --> 00:02:32.416 A:middle
Let's take a look at the

00:02:32.416 --> 00:02:33.526 A:middle
assistant editor mode.

00:02:34.926 --> 00:02:36.156 A:middle
What is interesting about this

00:02:36.196 --> 00:02:38.146 A:middle
mode in Playgrounds in Xcode is

00:02:38.146 --> 00:02:39.186 A:middle
that you can visualize your

00:02:39.186 --> 00:02:41.136 A:middle
results in more detail by using

00:02:41.136 --> 00:02:41.616 A:middle
a live view.

00:02:41.616 --> 00:02:45.426 A:middle
In this example I've created a

00:02:45.426 --> 00:02:47.126 A:middle
live view using UIView that

00:02:47.126 --> 00:02:48.256 A:middle
shows a welcome message.

00:02:49.246 --> 00:02:50.156 A:middle
But you could also use

00:02:50.156 --> 00:02:52.526 A:middle
UIViewController for iOS and

00:02:52.596 --> 00:02:54.046 A:middle
[inaudible] playgrounds and for

00:02:54.046 --> 00:02:56.426 A:middle
macOS playgrounds NSView and

00:02:56.426 --> 00:02:57.126 A:middle
NSViewController.

00:03:02.346 --> 00:03:03.336 A:middle
Now let me show you a short

00:03:03.396 --> 00:03:04.536 A:middle
snippet that demonstrates how to

00:03:04.536 --> 00:03:05.506 A:middle
show Live View.

00:03:06.576 --> 00:03:07.946 A:middle
First you need to import

00:03:07.976 --> 00:03:08.806 A:middle
PlaygroundSupport.

00:03:10.246 --> 00:03:11.836 A:middle
PlaygroundSupport is a framework

00:03:11.836 --> 00:03:13.626 A:middle
provided by Xcode to allow

00:03:13.626 --> 00:03:14.796 A:middle
playgrounds to interact with

00:03:14.826 --> 00:03:16.896 A:middle
Xcode, including support for

00:03:16.896 --> 00:03:17.726 A:middle
showing live views.

00:03:18.946 --> 00:03:20.086 A:middle
You import this playground

00:03:20.086 --> 00:03:21.656 A:middle
support framework so you can use

00:03:21.656 --> 00:03:22.056 A:middle
its API.

00:03:23.786 --> 00:03:24.546 A:middle
Once you've created a

00:03:24.546 --> 00:03:25.896 A:middle
viewController using the

00:03:25.896 --> 00:03:27.926 A:middle
standard UIKit or AppKit APIs,

00:03:28.566 --> 00:03:29.616 A:middle
you need to hand it over to the

00:03:29.616 --> 00:03:30.876 A:middle
PlaygroundSupport framework.

00:03:31.856 --> 00:03:33.266 A:middle
You do this by setting the Live

00:03:33.266 --> 00:03:34.776 A:middle
View property of the current

00:03:34.776 --> 00:03:36.016 A:middle
playground page to your

00:03:36.016 --> 00:03:36.666 A:middle
viewController.

00:03:37.656 --> 00:03:38.996 A:middle
This signals to Xcode that it

00:03:38.996 --> 00:03:40.126 A:middle
should show your viewController

00:03:40.126 --> 00:03:41.546 A:middle
in the assistant editor.

00:03:43.756 --> 00:03:44.736 A:middle
To give your playgrounds an

00:03:44.736 --> 00:03:46.316 A:middle
extra bit of polish, you can

00:03:46.316 --> 00:03:47.776 A:middle
include some markup text.

00:03:48.166 --> 00:03:49.626 A:middle
It is especially great when

00:03:49.626 --> 00:03:50.446 A:middle
you're making a playground to

00:03:50.446 --> 00:03:50.986 A:middle
share with others.

00:03:52.146 --> 00:03:53.476 A:middle
With markup you can include

00:03:53.616 --> 00:03:56.196 A:middle
stylized text, images, and video

00:03:56.196 --> 00:03:56.946 A:middle
in your playground.

00:03:58.116 --> 00:03:59.296 A:middle
Now let's take a quick

00:03:59.296 --> 00:04:00.686 A:middle
walkthrough what is possible

00:03:59.296 --> 00:04:00.686 A:middle
walkthrough what is possible

00:04:00.686 --> 00:04:01.336 A:middle
with markup.

00:04:03.826 --> 00:04:05.356 A:middle
Here I've included some markup

00:04:05.356 --> 00:04:06.736 A:middle
comments with text for a poem

00:04:06.736 --> 00:04:07.346 A:middle
I'm writing.

00:04:08.216 --> 00:04:09.436 A:middle
A markup comment is like a

00:04:09.436 --> 00:04:11.326 A:middle
regular comment but with a colon

00:04:11.326 --> 00:04:12.526 A:middle
after the forward slashes.

00:04:12.606 --> 00:04:14.516 A:middle
The rest of the comment is then

00:04:14.516 --> 00:04:17.786 A:middle
treated as markup text.

00:04:18.305 --> 00:04:19.576 A:middle
If you have multiple lines of

00:04:19.576 --> 00:04:21.375 A:middle
comments next to each other they

00:04:21.375 --> 00:04:23.536 A:middle
form one block of markup text.

00:04:25.536 --> 00:04:27.166 A:middle
You can also use multiline

00:04:27.166 --> 00:04:28.806 A:middle
comments by putting a colon

00:04:28.806 --> 00:04:30.096 A:middle
after the first asterisks.

00:04:32.086 --> 00:04:33.936 A:middle
Here's our markup in Xcode now.

00:04:34.716 --> 00:04:36.236 A:middle
It is showing the raw markup of

00:04:36.236 --> 00:04:36.996 A:middle
the poem I wrote.

00:04:38.106 --> 00:04:39.766 A:middle
To show it in its rendered form,

00:04:40.186 --> 00:04:41.526 A:middle
select the button in the top

00:04:41.526 --> 00:04:42.586 A:middle
right corner of the window,

00:04:42.976 --> 00:04:44.696 A:middle
which shows Xcode's Inspector.

00:04:45.926 --> 00:04:47.936 A:middle
Then select Render Documentation

00:04:48.216 --> 00:04:49.316 A:middle
under Playground Settings.

00:04:51.026 --> 00:04:52.396 A:middle
The lines in my poem are now

00:04:52.396 --> 00:04:52.876 A:middle
rendered.

00:04:55.486 --> 00:04:56.746 A:middle
Other interesting things you can

00:04:56.746 --> 00:04:57.866 A:middle
do with the markup are adding

00:04:57.866 --> 00:04:59.446 A:middle
headings to a Playground peach.

00:05:00.226 --> 00:05:01.356 A:middle
You can use headings to create

00:05:01.356 --> 00:05:02.676 A:middle
structure in your playground.

00:05:03.306 --> 00:05:04.476 A:middle
You can use number signs to

00:05:04.476 --> 00:05:06.146 A:middle
supply up to three levels of

00:05:06.146 --> 00:05:06.566 A:middle
heading.

00:05:07.666 --> 00:05:10.136 A:middle
In this example the title of my

00:05:10.136 --> 00:05:12.206 A:middle
poem "Roses are Red" as a first

00:05:12.206 --> 00:05:15.006 A:middle
level heading, the subtitle, "An

00:05:15.006 --> 00:05:16.706 A:middle
Ode to Markup" as a second level

00:05:16.706 --> 00:05:19.266 A:middle
heading, and the byline as a

00:05:19.336 --> 00:05:20.156 A:middle
third level heading.

00:05:21.476 --> 00:05:22.786 A:middle
Remember to add at least one

00:05:22.786 --> 00:05:24.006 A:middle
space between the number sign

00:05:24.006 --> 00:05:24.816 A:middle
and the heading string,

00:05:25.176 --> 00:05:25.996 A:middle
otherwise you'll have a number

00:05:25.996 --> 00:05:26.906 A:middle
sign connected to your heading

00:05:26.906 --> 00:05:27.416 A:middle
when rendered.

00:05:29.646 --> 00:05:30.666 A:middle
This is what the headings look

00:05:30.666 --> 00:05:31.936 A:middle
like rendered when included with

00:05:31.936 --> 00:05:32.916 A:middle
the lines in my poem.

00:05:33.786 --> 00:05:34.876 A:middle
You can see that the first level

00:05:34.876 --> 00:05:36.656 A:middle
heading is largest, followed by

00:05:36.656 --> 00:05:38.226 A:middle
the second level, and then the

00:05:38.226 --> 00:05:40.066 A:middle
third level heading.

00:05:40.776 --> 00:05:42.416 A:middle
You can also format the text in

00:05:42.416 --> 00:05:42.956 A:middle
your markup content.

00:05:43.066 --> 00:05:45.876 A:middle
You can wrap a string of

00:05:45.906 --> 00:05:47.926 A:middle
characters on a single asterisk

00:05:47.926 --> 00:05:49.226 A:middle
on each side to italicize the

00:05:49.226 --> 00:05:50.486 A:middle
text between the asterisks.

00:05:51.676 --> 00:05:53.286 A:middle
You can also use backticks to

00:05:53.286 --> 00:05:56.406 A:middle
display text with Code Font.

00:05:56.866 --> 00:05:58.156 A:middle
Finally, if you use two

00:05:58.156 --> 00:05:59.836 A:middle
asterisks instead of one the

00:05:59.836 --> 00:06:00.776 A:middle
text will be bold.

00:05:59.836 --> 00:06:00.776 A:middle
text will be bold.

00:06:01.826 --> 00:06:02.646 A:middle
Let's take a look at this

00:06:02.646 --> 00:06:03.036 A:middle
rendered.

00:06:05.346 --> 00:06:07.136 A:middle
You can see that red and blue

00:06:07.136 --> 00:06:08.096 A:middle
are italicized.

00:06:08.726 --> 00:06:11.196 A:middle
Markup is in Code Font and fun

00:06:11.236 --> 00:06:11.846 A:middle
is in bold.

00:06:13.966 --> 00:06:15.616 A:middle
Let's take a look at using lists

00:06:15.646 --> 00:06:16.346 A:middle
in markup.

00:06:17.346 --> 00:06:18.966 A:middle
If a markup comment starts with

00:06:18.966 --> 00:06:20.446 A:middle
a number followed by a period,

00:06:20.446 --> 00:06:22.306 A:middle
it will create an item in a

00:06:22.306 --> 00:06:24.406 A:middle
numbered list.

00:06:24.646 --> 00:06:25.966 A:middle
In this example, I've added the

00:06:25.966 --> 00:06:27.816 A:middle
lines of my poem to a numbered

00:06:29.326 --> 00:06:29.466 A:middle
list.

00:06:29.466 --> 00:06:30.536 A:middle
Here you can see the lines of my

00:06:30.536 --> 00:06:32.336 A:middle
poem rendered in a number list,

00:06:32.696 --> 00:06:34.906 A:middle
each line representing an item

00:06:34.906 --> 00:06:37.206 A:middle
in a numbered list.

00:06:37.486 --> 00:06:38.866 A:middle
You can also create a bullet to

00:06:38.866 --> 00:06:39.786 A:middle
list in markup.

00:06:40.806 --> 00:06:42.536 A:middle
A bulleted list is like a number

00:06:42.536 --> 00:06:43.996 A:middle
list except each line starts

00:06:43.996 --> 00:06:45.286 A:middle
with an asterisks instead of a

00:06:45.286 --> 00:06:45.616 A:middle
number.

00:06:47.726 --> 00:06:49.056 A:middle
This is how my poem in rendered

00:06:49.056 --> 00:06:51.076 A:middle
in a bulleted list with each

00:06:51.076 --> 00:06:52.516 A:middle
line in my poem represented as a

00:06:52.516 --> 00:06:54.276 A:middle
bulleted item in a bulletin

00:06:54.276 --> 00:06:54.446 A:middle
list.

00:06:57.076 --> 00:06:58.846 A:middle
Markup can also contain links.

00:06:59.746 --> 00:07:01.456 A:middle
In this example I've created a

00:06:59.746 --> 00:07:01.456 A:middle
In this example I've created a

00:07:01.456 --> 00:07:03.286 A:middle
link to roses and violets.

00:07:04.406 --> 00:07:05.736 A:middle
To create a link you wrap the

00:07:05.736 --> 00:07:07.536 A:middle
text in brackets and then place

00:07:07.576 --> 00:07:09.756 A:middle
the destination of the link in

00:07:11.196 --> 00:07:12.536 A:middle
parentheses after.

00:07:12.536 --> 00:07:13.546 A:middle
Another way you can create a

00:07:13.546 --> 00:07:15.466 A:middle
link is by using a reference.

00:07:16.036 --> 00:07:17.396 A:middle
In this example I've created a

00:07:17.396 --> 00:07:19.416 A:middle
reference named 1, but this can

00:07:19.416 --> 00:07:20.246 A:middle
be any string.

00:07:20.246 --> 00:07:21.306 A:middle
It doesn't have to be a number.

00:07:22.956 --> 00:07:24.416 A:middle
When creating and using a link

00:07:24.416 --> 00:07:26.036 A:middle
reference you wrap the name in

00:07:26.036 --> 00:07:26.786 A:middle
brackets.

00:07:27.196 --> 00:07:28.426 A:middle
When creating a reference you

00:07:28.426 --> 00:07:29.606 A:middle
add a colon and then the

00:07:29.606 --> 00:07:30.646 A:middle
destination to the link.

00:07:32.916 --> 00:07:34.446 A:middle
Here are the links represented

00:07:34.446 --> 00:07:37.226 A:middle
in rendered form, Roses,

00:07:37.226 --> 00:07:39.446 A:middle
Violets, and Fun are shown in

00:07:39.446 --> 00:07:40.836 A:middle
blue to represent a link.

00:07:43.086 --> 00:07:44.606 A:middle
Up to this point we treated a

00:07:44.606 --> 00:07:46.436 A:middle
playground as a single location,

00:07:47.136 --> 00:07:48.206 A:middle
but playgrounds can contain

00:07:48.206 --> 00:07:50.336 A:middle
multiple pages, each with their

00:07:50.336 --> 00:07:51.756 A:middle
own markup and code.

00:07:52.976 --> 00:07:54.746 A:middle
To create a new playground page,

00:07:55.036 --> 00:07:56.406 A:middle
select the playground and then

00:07:56.406 --> 00:07:57.426 A:middle
open the file menu.

00:07:58.026 --> 00:07:59.496 A:middle
Select New, then Playground

00:07:59.496 --> 00:07:59.926 A:middle
Page.

00:08:01.136 --> 00:08:02.086 A:middle
You could also create a

00:08:02.206 --> 00:08:03.586 A:middle
playground page by control

00:08:03.586 --> 00:08:05.206 A:middle
clicking on the playground and

00:08:05.206 --> 00:08:06.296 A:middle
then selecting New Playground

00:08:06.296 --> 00:08:06.796 A:middle
Page.

00:08:07.496 --> 00:08:10.246 A:middle
You can create links in your

00:08:10.246 --> 00:08:11.966 A:middle
markup, which navigate between

00:08:11.966 --> 00:08:12.296 A:middle
pages.

00:08:12.296 --> 00:08:15.636 A:middle
To go to the previous page, you

00:08:15.636 --> 00:08:16.516 A:middle
can create a link where the

00:08:16.516 --> 00:08:18.306 A:middle
destination is @previous.

00:08:18.306 --> 00:08:21.036 A:middle
To go to the next page you can

00:08:21.036 --> 00:08:21.686 A:middle
create a link where the

00:08:21.686 --> 00:08:23.186 A:middle
destination is @next.

00:08:24.576 --> 00:08:25.996 A:middle
Finally, if you want to navigate

00:08:25.996 --> 00:08:27.866 A:middle
to a specific page, you create a

00:08:27.866 --> 00:08:28.896 A:middle
link where the destination is

00:08:28.896 --> 00:08:30.656 A:middle
the file name for that page

00:08:30.976 --> 00:08:32.515 A:middle
without the extension and by

00:08:32.515 --> 00:08:34.395 A:middle
replacing any spaces or special

00:08:34.515 --> 00:08:36.186 A:middle
characters with their percent in

00:08:36.186 --> 00:08:36.946 A:middle
coded form.

00:08:39.626 --> 00:08:40.716 A:middle
You can also imbed some

00:08:40.716 --> 00:08:41.895 A:middle
additional content to make you

00:08:41.895 --> 00:08:43.436 A:middle
playgrounds even more powerful.

00:08:44.536 --> 00:08:46.066 A:middle
You can add additional Swift

00:08:46.066 --> 00:08:47.426 A:middle
files to the sources folder,

00:08:47.756 --> 00:08:48.976 A:middle
which is at the top level of the

00:08:48.976 --> 00:08:49.506 A:middle
playground.

00:08:50.816 --> 00:08:52.526 A:middle
Each page also has its own

00:08:52.596 --> 00:08:53.336 A:middle
sources folder.

00:08:54.296 --> 00:08:56.086 A:middle
Sources are compiled as separate

00:08:56.086 --> 00:08:57.466 A:middle
modules where they are

00:08:57.466 --> 00:08:58.536 A:middle
automatically imported where

00:08:58.536 --> 00:09:00.036 A:middle
visible so you don't have to

00:08:58.536 --> 00:09:00.036 A:middle
visible so you don't have to

00:09:00.036 --> 00:09:01.386 A:middle
handle import statements.

00:09:02.456 --> 00:09:03.576 A:middle
Since these are compiled as

00:09:03.616 --> 00:09:05.536 A:middle
separate modules, you can use

00:09:05.536 --> 00:09:07.486 A:middle
